   "source": "{\"cells\":[{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Project 6 — Local Email Reply Assistant\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Classify Email Intent and Draft Context-Aware Replies\\n\",\"\\n\",\"**Goal:** Build an assistant that classifies emails by intent and urgency,\\n\",\"then drafts replies with tone controls — all locally with Ollama.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"**Stack:** Ollama · LangChain · Jupyter\\n\",\"\\n\",\"### What You'll Learn\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. Intent classification — categorize emails by type\\n\",\"2. Urgency detection — flag high-priority messages\\n\",\"3. Structured JSON output\\n\",\"4. Reply generation with tone controls\\n\",\"5. Routing logic for different intents\\n\",\"\\n\",\"### Prerequisites\\n\",\"\\n\",\"- Ollama running with `qwen3:8b` pulled\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# !pip install -q langchain langchain-ollama langchain-core\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 1 — Verify Ollama and Configure LLM\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import requests, json\\n\",\"from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama\\n\",\"from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\\n\",\"from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\\n\",\"\\n\",\"try:\\n\",\"    r = requests.get(\\\"http://localhost:11434/api/tags\\\", timeout=5)\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"Ollama running — {len(r.json().get('models', []))} models\\\")\\n\",\"except: print(\\\"Start Ollama: ollama serve && ollama pull qwen3:8b\\\")\\n\",\"\\n\",\"llm = ChatOllama(model=\\\"qwen3:8b\\\", temperature=0)\\n\",\"print(\\\"LLM ready\\\")\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 2 — Sample Emails\\n\",\"\\n\",\"Diverse emails: questions, complaints, meeting requests, status updates, escalations.\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"emails = {\\n\",\"    \\\"technical_question\\\": {\\n\",\"        \\\"from\\\": \\\"dev@company.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"API rate limiting question\\\",\\n\",\"        \\\"body\\\": \\\"Hi team,\\\\n\\\\nI'm seeing 429 errors on /users during peak hours. Rate limit is 100 req/min. Can we increase for production?\\\\n\\\\nThanks, Alex\\\"\\n\",\"    },\\n\",\"    \\\"customer_complaint\\\": {\\n\",\"        \\\"from\\\": \\\"customer@gmail.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"Extremely frustrated with billing\\\",\\n\",\"        \\\"body\\\": \\\"I've been charged TWICE this month. Third time this happened. I want a full refund and I'm considering canceling.\\\"\\n\",\"    },\\n\",\"    \\\"meeting_request\\\": {\\n\",\"        \\\"from\\\": \\\"pm@company.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"Q3 Planning Session\\\",\\n\",\"        \\\"body\\\": \\\"Hi everyone,\\\\n\\\\nLet's schedule Q3 planning next week. Tuesday or Wednesday afternoon? About 90 minutes.\\\\n\\\\nBest, Sarah\\\"\\n\",\"    },\\n\",\"    \\\"status_update\\\": {\\n\",\"        \\\"from\\\": \\\"lead@company.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"Sprint 14 Update\\\",\\n\",\"        \\\"body\\\": \\\"Quick update:\\\\n- Auth migration: 90% done\\\\n- Dashboard: blocked on design review\\\\n- Perf tests: passed, 40% improvement\\\\n- Bug backlog: 23 down to 8\\\"\\n\",\"    },\\n\",\"    \\\"urgent_escalation\\\": {\\n\",\"        \\\"from\\\": \\\"ops@company.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"URGENT: Production database failover\\\",\\n\",\"        \\\"body\\\": \\\"Primary DB showing elevated errors. Failover at 14:32 UTC.\\\\n- Read: redirected\\\\n- Write: queued ~5 min\\\\n- ~2% getting 503\\\\n\\\\nNeed DB team immediately.\\\"\\n\",\"    },\\n\",\"}\\n\",\"\\n\",\"print(f\\\"Created {len(emails)} sample emails:\\\")\\n\",\"for key, email in emails.items():\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"  - {key}: '{email['subject']}'\\\")\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 3 — Classify Email Intent and Urgency\\n\",\"\\n\",\"LLM classifies each email returning structured JSON.\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"classify_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"\\\"\\\"Classify this email and return ONLY valid JSON:\\n\",\"{{\\n\",\"    \\\"intent\\\": \\\"question|complaint|request|update|escalation|other\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"urgency\\\": \\\"low|medium|high|critical\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"sentiment\\\": \\\"positive|neutral|negative|angry\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"key_topics\\\": [\\\"topic1\\\", \\\"topic2\\\"],\\n\",\"    \\\"requires_action\\\": true,\\n\",\"    \\\"summary\\\": \\\"one-sentence summary\\\"\\n\",\"}}\\n\",\"Return ONLY the JSON.\\\"\\\"\\\"),\\n\",\"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"From: {sender}\\\\nSubject: {subject}\\\\n\\\\n{body}\\\"),\\n\",\"])\\n\",\"\\n\",\"classify_chain = classify_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\"\\n\",\"classifications = {}\\n\",\"for key, email in emails.items():\\n\",\"    raw = classify_chain.invoke({\\\"sender\\\": email[\\\"from\\\"], \\\"subject\\\": email[\\\"subject\\\"], \\\"body\\\": email[\\\"body\\\"]})\\n\",\"    try:\\n\",\"        cleaned = raw.strip()\\n\",\"        if \\\"{\\\" in cleaned:\\n\",\"            cleaned = cleaned[cleaned.index(\\\"{\\\"):cleaned.rindex(\\\"}\\\")+1]\\n\",\"        parsed = json.loads(cleaned)\\n\",\"        classifications[key] = parsed\\n\",\"        print(f\\\"\\\\n--- {key} ---\\\")\\n\",\"        print(f\\\"  Intent: {parsed.get('intent')} | Urgency: {parsed.get('urgency')}\\\")\\n\",\"        print(f\\\"  Sentiment: {parsed.get('sentiment')} | Action: {parsed.get('requires_action')}\\\")\\n\",\"        print(f\\\"  Summary: {parsed.get('summary', 'N/A')}\\\")\\n\",\"    except json.JSONDecodeError:\\n\",\"        print(f\\\"\\\\n--- {key} --- (parse failed)\\\")\\n\",\"        classifications[key] = {\\\"intent\\\": \\\"unknown\\\", \\\"urgency\\\": \\\"medium\\\"}\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 4 — Route and Draft Replies\\n\",\"\\n\",\"Different intents get different tone instructions via a routing table.\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"reply_templates = {\\n\",\"    \\\"question\\\": \\\"Answer directly and helpfully.\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"complaint\\\": \\\"Acknowledge frustration. Apologize. State next steps.\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"request\\\": \\\"Confirm receipt. State availability. Suggest next steps.\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"update\\\": \\\"Acknowledge briefly. Highlight follow-up items.\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"escalation\\\": \\\"Acknowledge urgency. State actions. Provide ETA.\\\",\\n\",\"}\\n\",\"\\n\",\"reply_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"Draft a professional reply. Tone: {tone_guide}\\\\nKeep concise.\\\"),\\n\",\"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"Original from {sender}:\\\\nSubject: {subject}\\\\n\\\\n{body}\\\"),\\n\",\"])\\n\",\"\\n\",\"reply_chain = reply_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\"\\n\",\"for key, email in emails.items():\\n\",\"    cls = classifications.get(key, {})\\n\",\"    intent = cls.get(\\\"intent\\\", \\\"other\\\")\\n\",\"    tone = reply_templates.get(intent, \\\"Be helpful and professional.\\\")\\n\",\"    reply = reply_chain.invoke({\\\"sender\\\": email[\\\"from\\\"], \\\"subject\\\": email[\\\"subject\\\"], \\\"body\\\": email[\\\"body\\\"], \\\"tone_guide\\\": tone})\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{'='*60}\\\")\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"RE: {email['subject']} [{intent.upper()}]\\\")\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"{'='*60}\\\")\\n\",\"    print(reply[:400])\\n\",\"    if len(reply) > 400: print(\\\"...\\\")\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 5 — Tone Variants\\n\",\"\\n\",\"Generate different-toned replies to the complaint email.\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"complaint_email = emails[\\\"customer_complaint\\\"]\\n\",\"tones = {\\n\",\"    \\\"empathetic\\\": \\\"Be deeply empathetic and apologetic.\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"formal\\\": \\\"Be formal and corporate.\\\",\\n\",\"    \\\"solution_focused\\\": \\\"Skip apologies. Focus on solution and timeline.\\\",\\n\",\"}\\n\",\"\\n\",\"for tone_name, instruction in tones.items():\\n\",\"    reply = reply_chain.invoke({\\\"sender\\\": complaint_email[\\\"from\\\"], \\\"subject\\\": complaint_email[\\\"subject\\\"], \\\"body\\\": complaint_email[\\\"body\\\"], \\\"tone_guide\\\": instruction})\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"\\\\n--- Tone: {tone_name} ---\\\")\\n\",\"    print(reply[:300])\\n\",\"    if len(reply) > 300: print(\\\"...\\\")\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 6 — Edge Cases\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"edge_cases = {\\n\",\"    \\\"ambiguous\\\": {\\\"from\\\": \\\"x@test.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"Hey\\\", \\\"body\\\": \\\"Can you look at this?\\\"},\\n\",\"    \\\"spam\\\": {\\\"from\\\": \\\"deals@promo.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"WINNER!!\\\", \\\"body\\\": \\\"Click here to claim!\\\"},\\n\",\"    \\\"empty\\\": {\\\"from\\\": \\\"a@b.com\\\", \\\"subject\\\": \\\"(no subject)\\\", \\\"body\\\": \\\"\\\"},\\n\",\"}\\n\",\"\\n\",\"print(\\\"=== Edge Cases ===\\\\n\\\")\\n\",\"for name, email in edge_cases.items():\\n\",\"    raw = classify_chain.invoke({\\\"sender\\\": email[\\\"from\\\"], \\\"subject\\\": email[\\\"subject\\\"], \\\"body\\\": email[\\\"body\\\"]})\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"--- {name} ---\\\")\\n\",\"    print(f\\\"  Output: {raw[:200]}\\\\n\\\")\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Limitations\\n\",\"\\n\",\"| Aspect | Issue | Fix |\\n\",\"|--------|-------|-----|\\n\",\"| JSON reliability | Malformed JSON | Retry with error feedback |\\n\",\"| Intent ambiguity | Some emails don't fit | Add confidence scores |\\n\",\"| Tone control | Imperfect following | Use few-shot examples |\\n\",\"| Context loss | No thread history | Add conversation memory |\"]},{\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## What You Learned\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. Intent classification with structured JSON\\n\",\"2. Urgency detection for routing\\n\",\"3. Response routing by intent\\n\",\"4. Tone control with variants\\n\",\"5. Edge case handling\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Exercises\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. Add real emails (anonymized) and test\\n\",\"2. Build a priority queue by urgency\\n\",\"3. Add thread awareness\\n\",\"4. Use Pydantic for strict validation\\n\",\"\\n\",\"---\\n\",\"\\n\",\"*Next: **07 — Local Research Paper Explainer***\"]}],\"metadata\":{\"kernelspec\":{\"display_name\":\"Python 3\",\"language\":\"python\",\"name\":\"python3\"},\"language_info\":{\"name\":\"python\",\"version\":\"3.10.0\"}},\"nbformat\":4,\"nbformat_minor\":4}\n"
  }
